|802dot11_protocols = bgn |defaulip = 192.168.1.1 |defaultlogin = admin |defaultpass = admin |defaultssid = ASUS |defaultssid_regex = ^ASUS$ |default_ch = |manuf = Askey |manuf_model = RTA7156W |manuf_rev = D61 REV6 |is_manuf = No |tpfirmware = |availability = common (US) |eoldate = |fccapprovdate = 06/08/2011 |estreldate = |estprice = |upc = 610839364695 |ean = |dx_sku = |newegg = |asin = B0054L6XHY |asin_country = |asin2 = |asin_country2 = |countrymanuf = China |buttons = |led = |dimensions = |weight = |wi1_if_name = |rad1chip1cpu = true |rad1oui = |rad1_ant_conn = U.FL,RP-SMA |rad1txchains = 1 |rad1rxchains = 1 |rad1sstreams = 1 |rad1stand = IEEE 802.11b/g/n |rad1n = 150 |rad1g = 54 |rad1b = 11 |rad1freq = 2.4 }}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== "RTA7156W-D61-REV6" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :OEM: [[Askey]] RTA7156W-D61 (REV6) The device is using [[TrendChip]] TC3162LE/TC3086 for the ADSL portion. :The board is using a mix of ''TAICON'' and ''Lelon'' capacitors. *Notes specs as 4MB FLA/32MB RAM for WiFi, 1MB FLA/2MB RAM for ADSL. :Possible 20:CF:30 OUI (on FCC EUT's MAC label [affixed to Ethernet ports]) ===Specifications=== *[http://www.natthapol89.com/2014/04/asus-dsl-n10-a1.html ''Asus DSL-N10 A1 Review'' on '''natthapol'''] :Router CPU: [[Ralink]] RT3050F @320MHz WiSoC :Router RAM: [[Winbond]] W9825G6JH-6 32MB (SDRAM) :Router Flash: ''Macronix'' MX25L3206EM2I-12G 4MB (SPI) :ADSL CPU: [[TrendChip]] TC3162LE-LQ128G (ADSL2+) :ADSL RAM: [[Winbond]] W9816G6IH-6 2MB (SDRAM) :ADSL Flash: ''Macronix'' MX25L8006EM2I-12G 1MB (SPI) :ADSL Chip: [[TrendChip]] TC3086-QFN64-EPG ==JTAG-Serial Info== ===Serial=== ====Info derived from==== {{SCollapse|cpuinfo, mtd, bootlog • >> |
